Privacy & GDPR
Privacy & GDPR
Webtrends Optimize, and Accelerate Group Limited are each referred to herein as “
Webtrends
Optimize
”.
Last Updated: 2nd May, 2024
PRIVACY STATEMENT
This privacy statement applies to
https://www.webtrends-optimize.com
and other subdomains
comprising Webtrends Optimize’s corporate web presence (together our “Corporate Websites”); as well as to
our Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) platforms owned and operated by Webtrends Optimize (our “SaaS Solutions”).
This privacy statement (“Statement”) explains how your personal information is collected, used, and
disclosed by Webtrends Optimize and its subsidiaries and affiliated companies (“Webtrends Optimize” or
“We”). It also describes the choices available to you regarding the use of, your access to, and how to
update and correct your personal information. It applies to all business clients of our products and
services and visitors to our websites. This Statement does not apply to household consumers, visitors to
Webtrends Optimize’s clients’ sites, and services, or employees. This Statement does not cover the practices
of any third parties or their services, including any social networking platforms you choose to use to
connect with Webtrends Optimize Corporate Websites or SaaS Solutions, or to business clients who use
Webtrends Optimize services to collect information from their customers. For information about third party
privacy practices, please consult their privacy policies.
Data Controller
The data controller for all personal data collected from European data subjects is Webtrends Optimize.
We can be contacted at:
Webtrends Optimize
Lawrence House,
45 High St,
Egham TW20 9DP
United Kingdom
Or via email at:
legal@webtrends-optimize.com
Purpose of Data Collection and Processing
With respect to its Corporate Websites, Webtrends Optimize collects various data as described further in this
document for the purpose of responding to your requests, for first party marketing, as well as to better
understand our clients and their interests.
With respect to its SaaS Solutions, Webtrends Optimize is a data processor for all personal data collected on
behalf of clients (“Client Data”) – clients, as data controller, determine the purpose and legal basis of
all data processing activities – and Webtrends Optimize is a data controller for all personal data of
client’s employees (“SaaS Solutions Users”) collected and processed during access to these solutions.
Recipients of Personal Data Collected
With respect to Webtrends Optimize Corporate Websites, all data collected is stored in secure applications
with access limited to business needs. No personal data is shared with third parties other than services
providers acting as Webtrends Optimize’s agents.
With respect to its SaaS Solutions, Webtrends Optimize does not provide any third party with access to Client
Data. Webtrends Optimize may share personal data of SaaS Solutions Users with service providers acting as
Webtrends Optimize’s agents (such as for email notifications).
Personal Information Requests by Public Authorities
In certain situations, Webtrends Optimize may be required to disclose personal data; a) in response to lawful
requests, such as to comply with a subpoena or other legal process, by public authorities including national
security and law enforcement; b) in the event that Webtrends Optimize files for bankruptcy; c) to protect
our rights; d) to protect your safety or that of others; e) to investigate fraud, or f) to respond to a
government request.
WEBTRENDS OPTIMIZE NOTICE ON THE EUROPEAN UNION DATA PROTECTION REGULATION
(GDPR)
This notice applies to the Webtrends Optimize (“Companies”). It is relevant to Customers using Webtrends
Optimize software (“System”) who conduct business with End Users that are citizens of the European Union
(“EU”), and are thereby governed by the EU GDPR in effect as of May 25, 2018.
SECURITY
Webtrends Optimize have a comprehensive and mature Information Security program and are committed to the
privacy and security of its Customers’ data. Any information processed through the System is securely
handled, solely accessed by authorized personnel, and treated as confidential. The Companies implement and
maintain appropriate technical, security, and organisational controls to protect all personal data against
unauthorized or unlawful processing and use, and against accidental loss, destruction, damage, theft or
disclosure.
END USER ABILITY TO OPT-OUT OR WITHDRAW CONSENT
It is each Customer’s obligation to obtain End User consents. The Companies do not operate the web site or
digital property that its Customers’ End Users interact with, and therefore do not display any consent
notices.
END USER ABILITY TO REQUEST DATA DELETION
End Users have the right to request that you delete any historical data you have stored about them. To delete
End User data, please submit a request to
support@webtrends-optimize.com
. Your request
will be processed within fifteen (15) calendar days and you will receive a confirmation response when it’s
complete.
DATA COLLECTION
In its default configuration, the System is configured to prevent the capture of any personally identifiable
information. However, to perform its intended function, the System has the capability to read specific End
User information. The Companies will not retain data longer than is necessary to fulfill the purposes for
which it was collected or as required by applicable laws or regulations.
INFORMATION WE
COLLECT
Here are a few ways we collect your information and the types of information we collect. We may also obtain
information from other sources. Information we collect may be in the form of personal information or
anonymised data. Anonymised data may be in the form of aggregate data. Aggregate data is information we
collect about a group or category of services or users from which individual user identities have been
removed. In other words, no personal information is included in aggregate data. Aggregate data helps us
understand trends in our users’ needs so that we can better consider new features or otherwise tailor our
products and services. This Policy does not restrict or limit our collection and use of aggregate data.
Information You Provide To Us
We collect personal information you give us. These are the general types of information we may collect from
you:
Registration and Profile Information
– When you register to use our service, to receive
information, to participate in our events, and create or update your forum profile, we may collect various
kinds of information about you. For example, we may collect: your name; postal address; phone numbers; fax
numbers and email address; your log-in ID and password; your title; company; and other profile information
you provide; demographic information; and information linked with your profile such as comments you may
post.
Submissions and Customer Service
– From time to time we may use surveys, contests, or
sweepstakes requesting personal information. Information we collect may include demographic information,
information about your personal interests, and your feedback as a valued client.
Information We Automatically Collect
When you visit our site or use our services, some information such as your computer’s operating system,
Internet Protocol (IP) address, access times, browser type and language, and the website you visited before
our Corporate Websites is logged automatically and stored in log files. We also collect information about
your usage and activity on our Corporate Websites. We may tie your IP address to information we
automatically collect on our Corporate Websites. We may also tie information we automatically collect with
personal information, such as your login ID and information you give us at registration. We use our own
products, and products of third parties acting on our behalf, to analyse, optimise, and improve our site. To
opt-out of online behavioural advertising, please visit
http://www.networkadvertising.org/managing/opt_out.asp
.
We will also collect information on your usage of the SaaS Solutions to ensure the security of the data we
collect on behalf of our clients. You cannot opt-out of this collection and processing as it is necessary to
ensure the security of the service we provide to our clients. The information is below
The End User’s browser agent-string (also known as the User Agent)
which experiment they are exposed to.
metrics we have decided to capture that are important to us.
IP address, if the feature is enabled.
Optimize user ID, an anonymous, randomised identifier.
The Court of Justice of the European Union ruled, under Case 582/14, Patrick Breyer v Germany, that IP
addresses are “personal data” in certain circumstances and stated IP addresses would only qualify as
personal data if the relevant individual provides additional details to the website operator (e.g., name,
email address, etc.) in the course of using the website. The System does not store such additional user
details.
Webtrends Optimize and our marketing partners, affiliates, analytics providers, and leads management
providers use cookies and similar tracking technologies to analyse trends, administer the site, track users’
movements around the site, and gather demographic information about our user base as a whole. We may receive
reports based on the use of these technologies by these companies on an individual as well as aggregated
basis.
Cookie Policy
– We use cookies for analytics, user experience and session tracking, as well
as ad and video tracking. Users can control the use of cookies at the individual browser level. If you
reject cookies, you may still use our site, but your ability to use some features or areas of our site may
be limited.
Click
here
to find out more about the types of cookies Webtrends Optimize uses.
Webtrends Optimize may also use device-recognition technologies combined with other identifiers to create
cross-browsers and cross-devices identities to provide you with better services.
Behavioural targeting/Re-targeting
– We partner with third parties to either display
advertising on our Corporate Websites or to manage our advertising on other sites. Our third party partners
may use technologies such as cookies to gather information about your activities on this site and other
sites in order to provide you advertising based upon your browsing activities and interests. If you wish to
not have this information used for the purpose of serving you interest-based ads, you may opt-out by
clicking
here
). Please note this does not opt you out
of being served ads. You will continue to receive generic ads.
Information We Obtain from Other Sources
Webtrends Optimize may collect information about you from third party sources and services. We may buy or
lease contact, marketing, and demographic data from brokers. Webtrends Optimize may also access certain
profile information such as friends, profile picture, etc. from social networking platforms and services
that you use to interact with Webtrends Optimize Corporate Websites and SaaS Solutions. We may combine that
third party information with information we collect directly from you.
USE OF PERSONAL
INFORMATION
We use personal information collected through our Corporate Websites and SaaS Solutions in the ways we tell
you in this Statement. For example, we may use your information to:
operate and improve our sites, products and services;
process and deliver contest entries and rewards (Corporate Websites only);
respond to your comments and questions and provide customer service;
contact you to request feedback about your experience with our products and services or learn about your
demographics, preferences and interests;
provide and deliver our products and services you use;
send you information related to our products and services you use, including confirmations, invoices,
technical notices, updates, security alerts, and support and administrative messages;
communicate with you about new contests, promotions and rewards, upcoming events and webinars, and other
news about products and services offered by Webtrends Optimize and our selected partners (Corporate
Websites only);
anonymise and aggregate personal information for different purposes. This could include market analysis,
traffic flow analysis and reporting, and to deliver relevant advertising and information based on click
stream data (Corporate Websites only);
customise or personalise your online experience, for example to pre-populate forms and display relevant
content;
customise or personalise advertising and communications to bring you relevant information about products
and services that may interest you (Corporate Websites only); and
protect, investigate and deter against fraudulent, unauthorised or illegal activity. We may also link,
combine or supplement your personal information with other personal information we get from third
parties such as a business directory. We do this to help understand your needs and provide you with
better products and services. We may also use your personal information in other ways than as listed
here, in which case, we will inform you.
Webtrends Optimize may store and process personal information in the U.S., EU member countries, and other
countries.
SHARING OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
Information You Share
We may engage third parties to provide forums that allow you to connect and share your profile, actions,
comments, content, and information publicly and with others. We are not responsible for the personal
information you choose to submit in these forums. To learn how the third party applications use your
information, please review their privacy policies. To request removal of your personal information from our
blog or community forum, follow the instructions in the section titled Your Information Choices and Changes
below. We may also allow you to connect and share on third party sites and services. For example, we use a
single sign-on service that allows you to sign into Webtrends Optimize forums using certain third-party
social networking login credentials. This allows you to link your existing social network profile to your
Webtrends Optimize account. Once connected, you will be able to share and post content on and with the
third-party site from Webtrends Optimize and share and interact with your friends.
Please be mindful of your own privacy needs as you choose with which third party services to connect, with
whom you connect, and what to share and make public. We cannot control the privacy or security of
information you choose to make public or share with others. If you share information about others, we
suggest you get consent for any information you may share about them.
Information We Share
Corporate Websites only – We do not sell and share your personal information with third parties other than as
follows:
in an aggregated form that does not directly identify you;
with your consent, for example, when you agree to our sharing your information with other third parties
for their own marketing purposes subject to their separate privacy policies;
with third party vendors, consultants and other service providers such as email service providers,
marketing service providers, blog service providers and forum service providers who are working on our
behalf and need access to your information to carry out their work for us, these service providers are
authorised to use your personal information only as necessary to provide these services to us;
when we do a business deal, or negotiate a business deal, involving sale or transfer of all or a part of
our business or assets. These deals can include any merger, financing, acquisition, or bankruptcy
transaction or proceeding. You will be notified via email and/or a prominent notice on our Corporate
Websites of any change in ownership or uses of your personal information, as well as any choices you may
have regarding your personal information.
RETENTION AND SECURITY OF YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
The security of your personal information is important to us. When you enter sensitive information (such as
log in credentials), we encrypt the transmission of that information using secure transport layer security
(TLS). We follow generally accepted industry standards to protect the personal information submitted to us,
both during transmission and once we receive it, including encryption in transit, strict access controls,
firewalls and intrusion detection systems, hardening and patching procedures, and malware protection. No
method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure, however.
Therefore, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
Webtrends Optimize retains personal information it collects as a data controller consistent with its data
retention policy. Retention of Client Data (defined below) is documented in Webtrends Optimize Data
Retention Policy.
LINKS TO 3RD PARTY SITES
Our Corporate Websites includes links to other websites, mobile sites, and/or mobile applications whose
privacy practices may differ from those of Webtrends Optimize. If you submit personal information to any of
those sites, your information is governed by their privacy policies. We encourage you to carefully read the
privacy policy of any site you visit.
Social Media Widgets
Our Corporate Websites includes certain social media features, such as the Facebook button. These features
may collect your IP address, may collect which page you are visiting on our Corporate Websites, and may set
a cookie to enable such feature to function properly. Social media features are either hosted by a third
party or hosted directly on our Corporate Websites. Your interactions with these features are governed by
the privacy policy of the company providing it.
TESTIMONIALS
We display personal testimonials of satisfied clients on our site in addition to other endorsements. With
your consent, we may post your testimonial along with your name. If you wish to update or delete your
testimonial, you can contact us at
legal@webtrends-optimize.com
