opt-out of our sharing your information with independent third parties.
As a user of Webtrends Optimize’s SaaS Solutions, you may not opt out of personal data collection, because
such data collection is required to ensure the security and integrity of the data we collect on behalf of
our clients. If you object to such data collection, please contact the client for whom you work.
INFORMATION WE COLLECT ON BEHALF OF OUR CLIENTS
Webtrends Optimize acts as a service provider for each of our clients, in that we provide our services for
the benefit of the client. Each of our clients uses Webtrends Optimize products and services to gather
information about their own customers and visitors to their sites and digital properties (Client Data). Each
client instructs us as to what types of Client Data it would like us to collect on its behalf.
Webtrends Optimize will retain personal data we process on behalf of our clients for as long as needed to
provide services to our clients, and as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes,
and enforce our agreements. Webtrends Optimize retains Client Data, including any personal data, we process
on behalf of our clients in accordance with the Webtrends Optimize Data Retention Policy (Exhibit B of
Webtrends Optimize
Subscription Service Agreement
).
If you are a customer of one of our clients and would no longer like to be contacted by one of our clients
that uses our service, please contact the client that you interact with directly.
Webtrends Optimize may transfer personal information to companies that help us provide our service. Transfers
to subsequent third parties are covered by the service agreements with our clients.
Webtrends Optimize acknowledges that you have the right to access your personal information. Webtrends
Optimize has no direct relationship with the individuals whose personal data it processes. An individual who
seeks access, who seeks to correct, amend, delete inaccurate data, or who seeks to withdraw consent to
further contact should direct his/her query to the applicable Webtrends Optimize client. If the client
requests Webtrends Optimize to remove the data, we will respond to their request within 30 days.
We treat Client Data as the property and confidential information of the applicable Webtrends Optimize
client. We reserve a limited right to disclose any collected data as required by law, a valid court order,
or other request from a governmental authority. Other than under such a limited right, we do not share
information collected for one client with our other clients or with any third party.
Webtrends Optimize follows our clients’ instructions on cookie placement. To control the placement of cookies
set while visiting our clients’ web sites, please consult these clients’ privacy statement and cookie
settings.
END USERS CONTACTING WEBTRENDS OPTIMIZE FOR PRIVACY INQUIRIES
Under GDPR, End Users have the right to contact the Companies directly. Contact information and instructions
can be found on our website below.
