GDPR FAQs
What is the GDPR?
The General Data Protection Regulation (“GDPR”) is a comprehensive EU
data protection law, which goes into effect on May 25, 2018. The GDPR expands the privacy rights of EU
individuals, and places heightened obligations on companies that process EU personal data in the context of
providing goods or services to those individuals.
For more details, check out this Guide to the GDPR published by the
UK Information Commissioner’s Office
.
As a Webtrends Optimize client, does the GDPR apply to me?
Companies within the EU, or
who process the personal data of EU residents in the context of providing goods or services, will need to
comply with GDPR. As a Webtrends Optimize client collecting data via our Software-as-a-Service (SaaS)
solutions, you are likely a data controller under the GDPR.
Clients will need to evaluate their obligations under the GDPR, in part, based on: (1) the type of client
data that you collect via Webtrends Optimize SaaS solutions, and (2) the legal basis on which you rely for
the collection of this client data.
What about Webtrends Optimize?
Webtrends Optimize serves as the data processor for the
data you collect via our SaaS solutions, as further described in this GDPR FAQ. For some limited data types
(e.g. your login data), Webtrends Optimize is the data controller.
What personal data is collected and processed via Webtrends Optimize’s
solutions?
Webtrends Optimize’s SaaS solutions collect a limited amount of personal data by
default – (1) IP address; and (2) randomly generated GUID. Clients have control over, and are responsible
for, any additional collection and use of personal data.
Clients should be aware that combining multiple data elements, even if not considered personal data when
taken alone, may result in them being considered personal data when combined.
Can I avoid collecting personal data when using Webtrends Optimize’s solutions?
Webtrends
Optimize provides functionality to allow clients to truncate IP addresses. In addition, clients may contact
Webtrends Optimize’s Technical Support team to discuss other options for minimizing the collection of
personal data.
Are there certain types of data that cannot be collected and processed via Webtrends Optimize’s
solutions?
Yes. Webtrends Optimize’s SaaS solutions are not intended for processing data
that could be legally considered sensitive in any applicable jurisdiction (e.g. government-issued
identification or credit card numbers). Webtrends Optimize calls this “Prohibited Data”, and the default
configurations of Webtrends Optimize’s tagging methods do not collect Prohibited Data. Webtrends Optimize
prohibits clients from using its solutions to collect, store, process, or analyse Prohibited Data, and does
not accept liability for Prohibited Data.
When does Webtrends Optimize delete client data?
Webtrends Optimize deletes client data,
including backups, within thirty (30) days following termination of the agreement. Please refer to Webtrends
Optimize’s Data Retention Policy (Exhibit B to Webtrends Optimize’s Terms of Subscription Service) for more
information about data retention during the term of the agreement.
Does Webtrends Optimize provide clients with the option to delete client data?
Webtrends
Optimize supports the deletion of client data; however, this needs to be done in conjunction with Webtrends
Optimize’s Technical Support team pursuant to a Statement of Work.
Does Webtrends Optimize utilise augmentation data?
Yes. Webtrends Optimize uses
augmentation data from NetAcuity and Device Atlas to provide additional geographical and device information
in reports.
Where is the data held?
Webtrends Optimize leverages data collection centres in
Australia, Netherlands, Dublin. All data is stored in Amsterdam.
Webtrends Optimize’s
Commitment to Data Protection
Robust Security Practices. Webtrends Optimize employs technical and organisational measures designed to
prevent unauthorised access, use, alteration, or disclosure of Client Data collected via Webtrends
Optimize’s SaaS solutions). Further, Webtrends Optimize has more than 15 years of experience in operating
highly secured SaaS solutions with security controls that are continuously updated to meet industry
standards and emerging threats. This is described in detail in
Webtrends Optimize’s Security Statement
.
For more information, please contact us at
legal@Webtrends-Optimize.com
.
